    • Method Detail

      • parseLayoutFile

        public void parseLayoutFile(String fileName)
        Parses all layout XML files in the given APK file and loads the IDs of the user controls in it. This method only registers a Soot phase that is run when the Soot packs are next run
        Parameters:
        fileName - The APK file in which to look for user controls

      • parseLayoutFileDirect

        public void parseLayoutFileDirect(String fileName)
        Parses all layout XML files in the given APK file and loads the IDs of the user controls in it. This method directly executes the analyses witout registering any Soot phases.<
        Parameters:
        fileName - The APK file in which to look for user controls

      • getUserControlsByID

        public Map<Integer,LayoutControl> getUserControlsByID()
        Gets the user controls found in the layout XML file. The result is a mapping from the id to the respective layout control.
        Returns:
        The layout controls found in the XML file.

      • getUserControls

        public soot.util.MultiMap<String,LayoutControl> getUserControls()
        Gets the user controls found in the layout XML file. The result is a mapping from the file name in which the control was found to the respective layout control.
        Returns:
        The layout controls found in the XML file.

      • getCallbackMethods

        public soot.util.MultiMap<String,String> getCallbackMethods()
        Gets the callback methods found in the layout XML file. The result is a mapping from the file name to the set of found callback methods.
        Returns:
        The callback methods found in the XML file.

      • getFragments

        public soot.util.MultiMap<String,soot.SootClass> getFragments()
        Gets the fragments found in the layout XML file. The result is a mapping from the activity class to the set of found fragments ids.
        Returns:
        The fragments found in the XML file.

      • getLoadOnlySensitiveControls

        public boolean getLoadOnlySensitiveControls()
        Gets whether this analysis shall only collect sensitive controls such as password fields
        Returns:
        True if this analysis shall only collect sensitive controls, otherwise false
